Q_DESC: A positive rational number is a real number which can be expressed as P/Q where P, Q are coprime positive intergers. The Chef is very hungry and can get food only if he solves the following question. "Given a number N, find the number of positive rational numbers less than 1 such that when expressed as P/Q, both P, Q are less than or equal to N". Please help the Chef in answering this question. The Chef promises to share the food with you.
